- "top-selling products" refers to the products with the highest total sales;
- "size distribution" refers to the frequency of different sizes available for each product;
- "average price of their respective brands" refers to the average price of all products within the same brand.

- "Leading in terms of revenue" refers to brands with the highest total revenue;
- "Insights into their average product prices" refers to the average price of products for each brand;
- "Stock quantities across different categories" refers to the total stock quantity of products in each category for each brand.

- 'Total sales revenue' is the sum of the total price of all sales for each brand;
- 'Sizes' include various measurements such as waist, hip, thigh, chest, sleeve length, shoulder width, inseam, and length;
- 'Sales' data includes the quantity sold and the total price of each sale.

- "Top-selling products" refers to products with the highest total revenue;
- "Cumulative revenue" is the running total of revenue for each brand, ordered by the total revenue of each product;
- The query provides insights into how different sizes and categories contribute to the overall sales performance of each brand.

- The term "top-selling" refers to the product with the highest total sales within each brand;
- The `sales_rank = 1` condition ensures that only the top-selling product for each brand is selected;
- The `founding_year` provides historical context about when the brand was established.

- "Top-selling sizes" refer to the sizes with the highest total sales for each product;
- "Product name" and "brand name" are used to identify the specific products and their brands;
- "Total sales" is the sum of the quantities sold for each product-size combination;
- "Price" is the price of the product.
